New Records: De'Aaron Fox scored 109 points over a two-game span, breaking the franchise record previously held by DeMarcus Cousins.
Key Match Events: The Kings trailed 89-78 in the third quarter but came back in the fourth to take a 118-116 lead on a Jordan McLaughlin 3-pointer with a minute left to play.
Others: DeMar DeRozan, Malik Monk and Domantas Sabonis were sidelined for Sacramento, and Taylor Hendricks and Walker Kessler did not play for the Jazz.
